document.title: 2023 Indiana Academic Standards: Kindergarten - Grade 5 Physical Education

68398A9EC26D42A5AC793D66012E62CD.description:
Understands that physical activities can foster cooperation and
connection to enhance relationships among a diverse group of peers.

0D0EC0CEA78C496C96A894F33C9DA46C.description:
Identifies and compares physical activities that provide self-expression,
confidence, and challenge.

AEE9114EF3FE44729B5835043BFB8A64.description: Recognizes the value of “good health balance”.

54A9862C09504A238A189F8AC3420899.description: Valuing Health, Enjoyment, Challenge, Self Expression, and Social Interaction

EC5708C93899422183D3254E7083F773.description:
The physically literate individual recognizes the value of physical activity for health,
enjoyment, challenge, self expression and/or social interaction.

5CC75F8EE6E04481AEC685E2ECE9AC59.description:
Works independently and safely in physical education, including equipment
use.

9D5766E8061A4FB994D19F0E37758EA8.description:
Accepts responsibility and consequences for following rules and protocols for
class activities.

5BBE77745A4A40C494E82CDE8C5F867A.description: Works with others in partner activities.

54C27D21C87D42C8931B609D08F0DE4B.description: Accepts specific corrective feedback from the teacher.

B4EE6705287B4EFABC669DDEF70A36DC.description: Accepts responsibility and consequences for following rules and protocols.

F408E16C866A419897071D4188DADE28.description: Practices skills with minimal teacher prompting.

94A319F214C8496589092231FB827E58.description:
The physically literate individual exhibits responsible personal and social behavior
that respects self and others.

04250E392F6E4E4895C17A90BF2FA85E.description: Recognizes the “good health balance” of nutrition and physical activity.

25D61B67CD3E4CCBB91D914E5F161F85.description:
Recognizes structure and function of the circulatory and respiratory system
(such as lungs help with breathing).

745B10A291C5445A85F65FD7B0558E9D.description: Developmentally appropriate/ emerging outcomes first appear in grade three.

55F546D4B61E40B1B34508CAD0BE0F18.description: Identifies physical activities that contribute to fitness.

3E3CC27BF99847E1849618099981AF1C.description:
Recognizes the use of the body as resistance (such as holding the body in
plank position, bear crawl, crab walk, etc.) for developing strength and endurance.

D4240BC01B5D4D8C87617FBC2EB119B6.description:
Actively engages in physical education class in response to instruction and
practice.

6B1E7FFE06F44747BF5553BB76FD3254.description:
Describes large motor and/or manipulative physical activities for participation
outside physical education class (such as before and after school, at home, at the
park, with friends and family).

6CFA204CB4C944BC9785DF2938312220.description:
The physically literate individual demonstrates the knowledge and skills to achieve
and maintain a health-enhancing level of physical activity and fitness.

91FDB74144CB4B708BAB10DB5389E34A.description: Developmentally appropriate/ emerging outcomes first appear in grade three.

143E684B312842A190232D26B9567F0D.description:
Varies time and force with gradual increases and decreases as an introduction to
agility and speed.

1406187FF8D94800925CD1482788D44C.description:
Combines shapes, levels and pathways into simple travel, dance and gymnastics
sequences (such as demonstrating straight arms with a cartwheel; landing with soft
knees/slight flex when jumping down from a height).

66898B660BE843A190946E5ACF5999C0.description: Combines locomotor skills in general space to a rhythm.

DA336E6496E94FD38ADB60483BE99EDC.description:
The physically literate individual applies knowledge of concepts, principles,
strategies and tactics related to movement and performance.

E498F244896C459E8CBE1BA8D402499A.description: Jumps with a long rope five times consecutively with student turners.

BB0EE22DAB364031AAD295CC111097A1.description:
Jumps a self-turned rope consecutively forward and backward with a mature
pattern.

F6403759D97442D0B140C2A3307572D4.description: Strikes a ball off a tee or cone with a bat, using correct grip and body alignment.

EC1AA823019748A882AD9FE7FB90A240.description: Strikes an object upward with a short handled implement, using consecutive hits.

10E11A58831448B580186F6E1B2D25B6.description:
Volleys and strikes an object upward with open palms, forearms and shorthanded
hits.

CE27F27F7FDE4B3EB209E68C89E08202.description:
Performs emerging pattern while receiving with the non-preferred foot when
stationary.

6D135AD0238E4EC888E53E93AC3A3D91.description:
Dribbles with the feet in general space with control of the ball and body (such as
dribbling a ball in a soccer lead-up game).

C02D02BAC7EB4F629510AB2B12C3E0F4.description:
Demonstrates an emerging pattern while passing and kicking a moving ball with
the inside of the foot (such as passing the ball to a teammate in a soccer lead up game).

C8C49FDCD30D4537A9A3E8651AA99731.description:
Dribbles in personal and general space with preferred hand demonstrating a
mature pattern.

E64CEB48FBA340D1AF3D916461BA0CF2.description:
Catches a self tossed or well-thrown large ball with hands, not trapping or cradling
against the body.

7C090910A5A34788BD5F7276481D1AF4.description: Developmentally appropriate/emerging outcomes first appear in grade four.

9A93E1531DEC4363948D14BE535EB5C0.description:
Throws underhand and overhand using a developing and mature pattern to an area
or target.

9E4F270D799E48A2932D2D9E79BFB15E.description:
Transfers weight from feet to different body parts/bases of support for balance
and/or travel.

A134B14BD71B463C9E9FB0487865C336.description: Balances on different bases of support, combining levels and shapes.

A4AD13B7A8CA4B7299B209AEFA894F55.description:
Performs a sequence of non locomotor skills, transitioning smoothly from one skill
to another.

753B427F46C143A685E17F2186190B84.description:
Performs a teacher and/or student designed rhythmic activity with correct response
to simple rhythms.

ACB90D7780E147319FAE0C9B7203A5FD.description:
Demonstrates four of the five critical elements for jumping and landing in horizontal
and vertical planes using a variety of 1- and 2-foot take-offs and landings.

DAF1346FA2F049E6A886D2DC3D1BB2DD.description: Locomotor (Jumping and landing in a horizontal and vertical plane)

482B96A612EB4A4BA3B142DF0C38B92C.description: Performs mature patterns in locomotor skills (skip).

22EE59C48945443F8A213D751E026D69.description: Locomotor (Hopping, galloping, running, sliding, skipping, leaping, walking, running)

B7BA8453106F4B358011FEF0FCDDE8CF.description:
The physically literate individual will demonstrate competency in a variety of motor
skills and movement patterns.
